<div class="wy-control-group">
  <p class="edit-instruction"><strong>What are page layouts?</strong>Page layouts allow the user to choose a specific HTML layout to use for each {{model.name}} object in the CMS. These HTML files need to be included in the <code>/{{ model.id }}/layouts/</code> directory of the content object. By default, if no layout is selected, the <code>/{{model.id}}/individual.html</code> file will be used as normal.</p>
  <label for="Options">Page layouts</label>
  <div class="wy-control">
    {{#each option in editingControl.meta.options}}
    <label class="wy-checkbox">
      {{view "radio-button"
        name="default-template-option"
        selection=editingControl.meta.defaultValue
        value=option.value
      }}
      {{input value=option.label placeholder="Fancy layout"}}
      {{input value=option.value placeholder="layout_name.html"}}
      <span class="icon icon-plus-sign" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Add a new checkbox option below this one." {{action "addOption" editingControl.meta.options}}></span>
      <span class="icon icon-remove-sign" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Remove this checkbox option." {{action "removeOption" editingControl.meta.options option}}></span>
    </label>
    {{/each}}
  </div>
</div>
